HEADWORD: Najadaceae
<hw>Najadaceae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A monotypic family of
aquatic plants having narrow leaves and small flowers; same as
<fam>Naiadaceae</fam>; the naiad family.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <fam>Naiadaceae</fam>, family <fam>Naiadaceae</fam>,
family <fam>Najadaceae</fam>, naiad family.</syn>⟦br⟧
